# HITT command quoting

When documenting, suggesting, or generating **HITT** (`hitt.sh`) command examples, any option whose value is **more than one word** must be enclosed in **double quotes**.

Applies to (among others): `-m`, `-f`, `-k`, `-u`, `-t`.

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
bash hitt.sh -m "info ingress"
bash hitt.sh -m "info full"
bash hitt.sh -f "jenkins kubeconfig"
bash hitt.sh -k "get lastsuccessful"
bash hitt.sh -u "get secret my-secret helix-is"
bash hitt.sh -t "get tenant"

# ❌ BAD — shell splits the value; info sub-commands silently default to full
bash hitt.sh -m info ingress
bash hitt.sh -f jenkins kubeconfig
bash hitt.sh -u get secret my-secret
```

Single-word values do not require quotes: `-m post-hp`, `-f sat`, `-m info` (defaults sub-command to `full`).

When editing `docs/hitt/use-cases.json`, `README*.md`, help text in `hitt.sh`, or error messages, follow this convention consistently.
